'''Might Squadron''' was a [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighter]] [[Squadron/Legends|squadron]] of the [[Thyferran Home Defense Corps]] that served under the government instituted by [[Xucphra Corporation]] and headed by former [[Imperial Intelligence/Legends|Imperial Intelligence]] chief [[Ysanne Isard]], flying [[TIE/IN interceptor/Legends|TIE/IN interceptors]]. A green unit by the standards set by former [[Rogue Squadron/Legends|Rogue Squadron]] [[Pilot/Legends|pilot]] and [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] agent [[Erisi Dlarit]], the squadron's name became the subject of many jokes within the THDC, the popular refrain being that their name was the answer to the question "Will they fight?"

During the [[Battle of Thyferra]], that marked both the climax and resolution of the [[Bacta War]], Might Squadron was annihilated down to the last starfighter by Dlrit's former unit, the Rogues.

